Hell is more than a place, it's a state of the soul, so many people are "in Hell" in that sense, including living ones (most of us are), but the idea is that nothing has yet been decided, all suffering experienced is still temporary, the potential for salvation is not exhausted

Basically this means if your grandpa died in a state of hatred and sin, if you are able to love him regardless, and pray for his soul and the forgiveness of his sins every night, he too can be saved through your tears, thus we are called to pray for all dead and hope for them
